description:
Welcome to the Historic Red Brick Mansion!
 
Become a part of Ithaca's history when you live in this building that has been officially designated as an Ithaca Landmark. This Italianate Mansion dating from the 1890s retains much of its original charm and character, including high ceilings, oak floors and trim, and carved fireplace mantels. The house is now configured into five unique apartments, with a laundry room and trash room in the basement, and a large parking lot that fits 38 vehicles. This fabulous Collegetown location is close to Cornell, yet just outside the main commercial blocks, adding desirable privacy and quietness to an otherwise crowded neighborhood. 
 
Each 2-bedroom apartment has a private ground-floor entrance, two bedrooms, and one bathroom. The modern kitchen is equipped with a dishwasher, microwave, oven, and refrigerator. The carpeted living room is furnished with a small sofa, arm chair, coffee table, and a dining table and chairs. There is also a 50" mounted flat screen TV for tenants' enjoyment. Each bedroom is fully furnished with a full sized bed, dresser, bookcase, desk, and chair.
 
Our leases are for twelve months. All of our properties are designated as non-smoking. The rent includes heat and hot water. Apartments are wired for cable and internet. Our full time maintenance staff is available 24 hours a day. Assigned parking is available for an additional fee.
 
Please visit our website for floor plans and photos, a sample lease, and other important rental information.
 
For video tours, check out our YouTube channel!

Lakefront Paradise in Ithaca, NY - Your Dream Home Awaits! 

If you're an adventurer at heart and crave the breathtaking beauty of lakefront living, this rental is tailor-made for you! Welcome to your oasis of tranquility, nestled in the heart of Ithaca, NY. Take heed, non-intrepid souls, for only those with a spirit of exploration need read on! 

Key Features: 
 Parking Note: A winding driveway and a "mere" 65 steps separate you from this lakeside haven. In snowy conditions, you may want to channel your inner explorer and park on the street, embarking on a picturesque trek to your abode. (Though, last year's absence of snow might have you questioning the whims of climate change!)

 Furnished Comfort: This cozy abode comes fully furnished, ensuring your move-in process is seamless and hassle-free. Unpack and unwind in a space designed for both relaxation and inspiration.

 Amazing Lakefront Location: Wake up to the melodious symphony of waves lapping against the shore and the sun casting its golden hues over the water. Sit and enjoy coffee on the deck, wander to the edge of the dock, congregate around the firepit at night, and embrace the ever-changing vistas as the lake's colors shift with the seasons.

 No Short-Term Renting or Subletting: This treasure trove of a dwelling is seeking a long-term companion from either November or December 1, 2023 through April 30, 2024 (negotiable to extend through May 18 if needed). If you're seeking a home to create memories, be inspired, and embrace the beauty of Cayuga Lake, you've come to the right place.

 Pricing: All these wonders can be yours for a monthly rent of $2550, offering incredible value for an experience that's truly priceless.

 No Pets: As much as we adore furry friends, our abode must remain a haven for those of us with severe allergies. Rest assured, though, that the beauty of the surroundings will more than compensate for this restriction.

Act Fast: Opportunities like this are as rare as the gems they represent. Embrace the call of the lake and secure your spot in this remarkable lakefront house. Contact Maureen for info about rental requirements and to schedule a visit. (Do not stop by without an appointment, the house is occupied.) Dive into the serenity, adventure, and charm that only lakefront living in Ithaca can provide!

Two kayaks and one SUP (although lake temps are cold this time of year!) can be available. Available to rent either November or December through April. Negotiable to rent through May 18, 2024 at the latest. No pets, we have family members with severe allergies and we use the house part of the year. Tenant is to maintain yard, steps, driveway, etc. Exterior hose bibs to be turned/left off in winter. House is on septic, proper usage required. Lake homes in this area pull water from the lake. There is a chlorination system, but we recommend using bottled water for drinking. No smoking, no large parties (we live in a community and want to maintain good relations with neighbors). There is private parking and the lot was recently re-paved. Tenants should not use neighbor's yards or docks...our yard is a slice of heaven - there is really no need to go into the other yards, just want to make sure we mention it! This house has beach access into the lake and a private dock as well! Security deposit = one month's rent. Household income 3x rent and minimum credit score 650 (no cosigners). Background and credit check via RentSpree. This is not undergraduate housing.
